{
  "texts": [
    "Raw sequence data is mapped to a reference genome and then analyzed by DeepVariant to identify the locations of variations such as single nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) and short insertions and deletions (indels) (DePristo and Poplin 2017).",
    "The newer versions of this tool can accept the raw sequence data from Illumina or PacBio sequencing and Oxford Nanopore (DePristo and Poplin 2017; Carroll 2020).",
    "One of the major limitations of DeepVariant is that it is well optimized to germline variants.",
    "So, it may not be as suitable for somatic variant calling in cancer genomics.",
    "DeepTrio further expanded the functionality of DeepVariant."
  ]
}